  "body": "Output of `helm version`:\r\n`version.BuildInfo{Version:\"v3.0.0-alpha.2\", GitCommit:\"97e7461e41455e58d89b4d7d192fed5352001d44\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", GoVersion:\"go1.12.7\"}`\r\n\r\nIn former versions like `v2.14.2` the missing trailing slash  was supported when executing following command:\r\n`helm fetch tekton --repo https://storage.googleapis.com/chartmuseum.jenkins-x.io`\r\n\r\nNow with helm3 I get following error:\r\n`helm fetch tekton --repo https://storage.googleapis.com/chartmuseum.jenkins-x.io\r\nError: failed to fetch https://storage.googleapis.com/charts/tekton-0.0.42.tgz : 403 Forbidden`\r\nbecause he seems to dismiss the `repo` flag alltogether. When executing\r\n`helm fetch tekton --repo https://storage.googleapis.com/chartmuseum.jenkins-x.io/` it works.\r\n\r\nThis gets in conflict with the `jx` binary of Jenkins X which produces repo-urls without the trailing slashes.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if missing trailing slashes would be supported again.",
